modmenu.descriptionTranslation.worldgend: A mod that aids in the development of world generation data packs and mods. Allows reloading worldgen data packs in-game and resetting chunks. Colors jigsaw blocks by name and target.
modmenu.summaryTranslation.worldgendevto: A mod that aids in the development of world generation data packs and mods.
gamerule.minecraft.reload_registries.des: Worldgen Devtools: Extend the /reload and /datapack enable|disable commands to reload all registries, such as worldgen definitions.
gamerule.minecraft.sync_after_registry_r: Worldgen Devtools: Syncronize changes to all clients (including in singleplayer) after a registry reload, such as biome colors and trim patterns. Disabling this enables faster reloads.
gamerule.minecraft.max_chunk_status.desc: Worldgen Devtools: The maximum worldgen status of newly generated chunks.
gamerule.minecraft.apply_processor_lists: Worldgen Devtools: Apply configured processor lists to generated jigsaw structures.
gamerule.minecraft.keep_jigsaws.descript: Worldgen Devtools: Keep Jigsaw blocks after jigsaw structure generation.
gamerule.minecraft.apply_gravity_process: Worldgen Devtools: Apply the gravity processor to terrain matching jigsaw structure pieces.
gamerule.minecraft.save_chunks.descripti: Worldgen Devtools: Turning this OFF will disable any world saving, so that reloading the world will regenerate it. Already saved chunks are not deleted.
